TASK_SCHEMA_VERSION=3
TASK_ID=190
TASK_TITLE=Fix send-keys first-character eaten after Escape
TASK_STATUS=done
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_TEAM=W3
TASK_DESCRIPTION=BUG: When Boss or any role sends tmux send-keys with Escape immediately before, the first character of the next send-keys is consumed by the Escape sequence. Example: send-keys Escape then send-keys '/compact' Enter → arrives as 'ompact'.

ROOT CAUSE: tmux Escape key has a delay (escape-time setting, default 500ms). When send-keys fires the text immediately after Escape, tmux interprets the first character as part of the escape sequence.

FIX OPTIONS:
1. Add a small sleep (50-100ms) between Escape and the text send-keys
2. Use tmux copy-mode -q instead of Escape to cancel current state
3. Combine into a single send-keys call with proper escaping
4. Set escape-time to 0 in the Doey session tmux config

SCOPE: Fix everywhere we do Escape + send-keys — search all hooks, skills, agents, and shell scripts for this pattern. Must work on fresh install.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:Dispatch to W3 — fix send-keys first-char bug:done\n2:W3.1: Fix Escape+send-keys in shell/ (doey.sh + helpers):done\n3:W3.2: Fix Escape+send-keys in .claude/hooks/:done\n4:W3.3: Fix Escape+send-keys in .claude/skills/ + agents/*.md.tmpl:done\n5:W3.4: Add escape-time 0 to session config + run tests + expand templates:done
